The paper discusses a new approach for efficient graph computation on billion-scale graphs, which is a common problem in distributed computing (cs.DC). The approach involves optimizing I/O operations and exploiting modern hard drives and processors, which are topics related to databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new programming model for implementing graph algorithms, which falls under computational engineering (cs.CE) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
